The DaimlerChryler Asia Management Associate Program (AMAP) is a comprehensive management training program for automotive engineers and business administrators. It helps fulfill the need of highly qualified, motivated and cosmopolitan Chinese top talents for DaimlerChrysler\'s rapid and dynamic business development in China. 
With our Asia Management Associate Program, we offer Chinese native speaking young professionals a unique opportunity to start a career with bright prospects. The program is open to university graduates with 1-3 years professional experience. Successful candidates from our selection process are appointed as Management Associates. Those who have successfully completed the AMAP Program may be offered challenging positions within the DaimlerChrysler Group in China. 
What we offer you 
&amp;#8226;  Significant and challenging assignments in different DaimlerChrysler business units with a period of 12- 18 months to prepare you for a world-class business career 
&amp;#8226;  Rotation inside and outside China, which provides you with an international and interdisciplinary background 
&amp;#8226;  an induction program in Germany to give you an overview of the company value 
&amp;#8226;  Training courses to improve your personal, communicative, and business skills 
&amp;#8226;  A personal mentor to support you in your career development 
New positions for a second round selection! 
&amp;#8226;  After-sales Department, Product Quality Reporting (working location: Beijing) 
&amp;#8226;  Executive Assistant (working location: Fuzhou) 
&amp;#8226;  Product Marketing (working location: Fuzhou) 
What we expect from you 
&amp;#8226;  You should be a Chinese native speaking young professional with 1- 3 years working experience 
&amp;#8226;  University degree or above with excellent academic record, preferable major in automotive engineering, sales &amp; marketing, business administration or related 
&amp;#8226;  Excellent English Communication ability (written and spoken) 
&amp;#8226;  Self-reliant working style 
&amp;#8226;  Team spirit and good interpersonal skills 
&amp;#8226;  Good planning and organizational skills 
&amp;#8226;  Results-oriented with a pleasant and dynamic personality 
Interested? 
If you think you have the qualifications, motivation, drive and abilities to help us face the challenges of a global company, we invite you to apply online before September 15, 2005. 
